===Etymology 1===
From the Athenian lawmaker {{w|Draco (lawgiver)|Draco}}, known for making harsh laws.

====Adjective====
{{en-adj}}

# Very [[severe]] or [[strict]].
#: ''The Soviet regime was '''draconian'''.''
#: ''The mayor announced '''draconian''' budget cuts today.''
